First, we will determine the value of £100 when express in dollars. We can see in Figure 21.1 that the value of a U.K. pound when express in dollar is **$ 1.6893.** Hence, we will multiply the $100 to the value of pounds in U.S. dollar to determine how many pounds we can get.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Pounds (£)} &= \text{£ in dollar} \times {{\text{Dollars to exchange}}}\\
&= \text{\$ 1.6893} \times {{\text{\$100}}}\\
& = \boxed{\text{\$168.93}}
\end{aligned}$$
